    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-apricots-and-tamarind-curry-with-kachumber/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-apricots-and-tamarind-curry-with-kachumber/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once melted, add<strong> </strong>most of the <strong>sliced onion</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 8-10 min or until softened and caramelised</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-apricots-and-tamarind-curry-with-kachumber/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Chop your<strong> creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-apricots-and-tamarind-curry-with-kachumber/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong> in 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[600ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [800ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>then add your <strong>diced apricots</strong>, <strong>tamarind paste</strong> and <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>apricots & tamarind stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-apricots-and-tamarind-curry-with-kachumber/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong>,<strong> curry powder</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> to the softened onion and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the <strong>apricots & tamarind stock</strong>, give everything a good mix up, then add the <strong>chicken </strong>and increase the heat to high</p><p>Cook, covered, for 18 min (turning half way) or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has reduced to a curry-like consistency</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-apricots-and-tamarind-curry-with-kachumber/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Dice your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>and <strong>cucumber</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>diced</strong> <strong>tomato</strong>, <strong>diced</strong> <strong>cucumber </strong>and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>sliced onion</strong> in a large bowl with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>coriander</strong> just before serving \u2013 this is your<strong> kachumber</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-apricots-and-tamarind-curry-with-kachumber/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the pan from the heat and shred the<strong> cooked chicken</strong> apart in the pan using two forks \u2013 this technique is known as 'pulling'</p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>chicken, apricots & tamarind curry</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>chicken, apricots & tamarind curry</strong> over the <strong>basmati rice</strong> with the <strong>kachumber </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
